- Newtonsoft.Json 13.0.4
- System.IO.Compression.ZipFile 4.3.0

## Installation

### 1. Clone Repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/SURERAKESHKUMAR/migration_accelerator-1.git
cd migration_accelerator-1
2. Install Dependencies
bash
dotnet restore
3. Database Configuration
Database credentials are configured in appsettings.json. Update connection parameters for your environment:

JSON
{
  "ConnectionStrings": {
    "DefaultConnection": "Server=YOUR_SERVER;Database=migration_accelerator;User Id=YOUR_USER;Password=YOUR_PASSWORD;"
  },
  "AWS": {
    "Region": "us-east-1",
    "SecretName": "your-secret-name"
  }
}
4. AWS Secrets Manager Setup
The application uses AWS Secrets Manager for credential management. Configure your secret:

bash
# Set AWS credentials
aws configure

# Create/Update secret in Secrets Manager
aws secretsmanager create-secret \
  --name migration_accelerator/secrets \
  --secret-string '{"DbPassword":"your-password","ApiKey":"your-key"}'
5. Initialize Database
The application automatically creates required tables on first run via Entity Framework Core migrations:

bash
dotnet ef database update
6. Build Application
bash
dotnet build
